. I want to make sure we list providers who support API integrations\nso developers can integrate them with their apps.\n\n## Notification Infrastructure Platforms\n\n  * courier.com - Single API for push, in-app, email, chat, SMS, and other messaging channels with template management and other features.\n  * engagespot.co - Multi-channel notification infrastructure for developers with a prebuilt in-app inbox and no-code template editor.\n  * knock.app - Notifications infrastructure for developers. Send to multiple channels like in-app, email, SMS, Slack, and push with a single API call.\n  * novu.com - The open-source notification infrastructure for developers for managing all communication channels in one place: Email, SMS, Direct, In-App and Push.\n\n## Realtime API Providers\n\n  * ably.com - Realtime messaging service with presence, persistence and guaranteed delivery.\n  * pusher.com - Realtime messaging service.\n  * pubnub.com - Swift, Kotlin, and React messaging at 1 million transactions each month. Transactions may contain multiple messages.\n\n## Marketing Communication Providers\n\n  * braze.com - Cross-channel customer engagement platform\n  * customer.io - Personalised marketing automation platform\n  * onesignal.com - Unlimited free push notifications. Supports email.\n  * pushwoosh.com - Omnichannel customer engagement platform\n\n## Push notification APIs\n\n  * firebase.google.com - Cross-platform messaging solution that lets you reliably send messages at no cost.\n  * pushengage.com - The #1 push notification platform for web and mobile devices\n\n## Chat APIs\n\n  * comechat.com - Build real time chat, voice and video calling experience with CometChat's flexible SDKs, APIs & UI Kits.\n  * sendbird.com - Messaging-as-a-service API that provides chat, voice, and video messaging for mobile apps and websites.\n\n## Email APIs\n\n  * mailgun.com - Transactional Email APIs that enable you to send, receive, and track emails.\n  * resend.com - The most developer friendly email API\n  * sendgrid.com - API to send both transactional and marketing emails.\n\n## AMQP Providers\n\n  * cloudamqp.com - The largest fleet of RabbitMQ and LavinMQ clusters worldwide\n  * aws.amazon.com/amazon-mq - Managed message broker service for Apache ActiveMQ and RabbitMQ on AWS.\n\n## About\n\nList of notification infrastructure providers for developers\n\n### Resources\n\nReadme\n\nActivity\n\n### Stars\n\n1 star\n\n### Watchers\n\n1 watching\n\n### Forks\n\n0 forks\n\nReport repository\n\n## Releases\n\nNo releases published\n\n## Packages 0\n\nNo packages published\n\n## Footer\n\n\u00a9 2024 GitHub, Inc.\n\nYou can\u2019t perform that action at this time.\n\n", "frontpage": true}
